access:
Entire home  1 bedroom one bathroom apartment at the garden level of my brownstone in Brooklyn.
with own private bathroom, small kitchen,  big garden.

The apt is 600 square feet (50 square meters)

Non smoking  inside  the apt please only in the back part of the garden.
additional_house_rules:
You can treat my place like your own precious home. Like you, I try to keep things clean, you will find it pleasantly prepared for your arrival. Like you, I know the value of my own and my neighbors' privacy, so I keep the noise down and enjoy some light music. No babies or small children are allowed to stay overnight because of the stairs. The apartment is not small children proof.  Please do not smoke inside the apartment. And no candles because of fire hazard.  Be careful with curlers and hair straighteners make sure they are safely stored and cooked down before that.
Also please refer to the extra guest fee after the first guest. Please add the number of guests at the booking.
Enjoy.
Thank you.
Amy
description:
You can reach both airports in under 40 minutes!

Times Square, Central Park, Javits Center, and the One World Trade Center are all accessible with just 1 train ride!

It's a great space to daydream, write or create.

My house is perfect for you to enjoy New York and make Brooklyn the center of your stay. It feels warm and cozy during cold weather, and cool and fresh for warmer days. Air conditioner in each room.

It's full of light in the gardensunshine and quiet.
It's a great space to daydream create or write.
All the wood of the house was recycled and it has kept some of its original spirit.
The garden has a bird sanctuary in the spring and summer. You will hear and see lovely birds sing.

We have one bedroom, a big  garden a private bathroom
And kitchen and is an entire apartment.

Also can be used for commercial shootings  use, I have had many blogs, fashion magazines and small crew films rent it. Only after inquiry no instant booking please.

The neighborhood is  a multicultural and multi ethnic landmark/historic.
Check Restsurant Saragina for more info, bar lunatico, peaches.

In the spring summer and fall  it's lovely but loses some of the appeal in the winter months as the flowers die. However we are 7 minutes walk to the A express to the city that can be reached in 15 minutes and 8 minutes to downtown Brooklyn and the Barclay center. 
Stuyvisan heights is the  landmark part of Bedstuy.

Entire home  1 bedroom one bathroom apartment at the garden level of my brownstone in Brooklyn.
with own private bathroom, small kitchen,  big garden.

The apt is 600 square feet (50 square meters)

Non smoking  inside  the apt please only in the back part of the garden.

I keep an open connection with my guests but do not disturb them.
I introduce them to the house and explain restaurants, subway and neighborhood.
After that
They are free to
Contact me at any time.

I was one of the first hosts in paris with airbnb seven years ago.

I love to interact with guests from
Around the world.

I have been very lucky to meet amazing people.

This is a very pleasant neighborhood to stay in with lots of good finds all around!
The famous Saragina  restaurant, bakery ( fresh pasta,croissants and coffee!)and wine bar are one block away!
New French wine store in my street too, manny s wine.
Juice bar across the street.
Lebanese cafe One block away.
Organic big supermarket at the corner opening in January as well as a Japanese restaurant around the corner in February.

It's multicultural and famous for its jazz.

Bar lunatico with great music every night also one block up.
It's also open for breakfast and lunch.

It's a landmark area and Stuyvisan heights it's just beautiful!

It's a quiet neighborhood and just right to enjoy your rest after traveling around the city during the day.
An organic food store is two blocks away.

A French cafe is across the street  to my left ' George's andre' as well as Saraghina s and Manny s great breakfast!
A polish cafe  (Zabka) were you can drop luggages the whole day you go for 5 dollars per suitcase two minutes to my right.

An organic deli across the house is open till midnight.
As well as a new organic supermarket at the corner of my street and a French wine shop ' manny s wine' in my street.

My place is only a few short blocks away (6 minutes)from the  express A and local C train lines.
Bus stops are also conveniently located at both ends of my block.
Taxis frequent the neighborhood so there is always that option.
Other services like UBER and Lyft are easy to acquire too.

1 train ride to and from the One World Trade Center, The Javits Center, Times Square, and Central Park
15 min away from Barclays Center, Prospect Park Zoo, and The Brooklyn Botanic Garden
16 min away from Forest Park Golf Course,
16 minutes from the village in Manhattan.
19 minutes to Chelsea.
25 min away from Citi Field and US Open venues
30 minutes away from both JFK International Airport and LaGuardia Airport

Parking on the street is easy, and the neighborhood is easily accessible via different modes of transportation.
The A express train takes you to manhattan in 16 minutes.
The 1112 Fulton streetC train is three stops to fort Greene  and Brooklyn academy of music ( bam).

Great train only 6 minutes walk from me.
Express bus to Williamsburg across my street.(20 minutes ride).
